-- Indonesia's Bank Central Asia posts 24 pct rise in first-half profit
-- By Fathiyah Dahrul
-- Wed Jul 23, 2014 05:31AM EDT
-- None



JAKARTA, July 23 (Reuters) - Indonesia's PT Bank Central Asia Tbk <BBCA.JK> on Wednesday posted a rise of 24 percent in first-half net profit, lifted by strong net interest income.

Indonesia's biggest bank by market value reported net profit of 7.85 trillion rupiah ($682.9 million) for the six months ended June versus around 6.3 trillion rupiah a year earlier.